Metadata-Version: 1.0
Name: LDAP-Hopper
Version: 0.1.0
Summary: Simple access to LDAP Directory Information Tree.
Home-page: http://pypi.python.org/pypi/LDAP-Hopper/
Author: Brian Wiborg
Author-email: baccenfutter@c-base.org
License: LICENSE.txt
Description: ===========
        LDAP-Hopper
        ===========
        
        LDAP-Hopper is a simplistic Python binding for accessing an LDAP Directory
        Information Tree(DIT).::
        
            #!/usr/bin/env python
            from ldap_hopper import LdapNode
        
            # access the root-node
            LdapNode.SERVER = 'localhost'
            base_dn = 'dc=example,dc=org'
            bind_dn = 'cn=admin,dc=example,dc=org'
            bind_pw = 'secret'
            root = LdapNode(base_dn, bind_dn, bind_pw)
        
            # show attributes of root-node
            root.load_attrs()
            print root.attrs
        
            # get childs of root
            print root.get_childs()
        
            # get subtree of root
            print root.get_subs()
        
        
Platform: UNKNOWN
